Online Research to make to do app :

Set Up Your Environment:
---------------------------
Install necessary libraries such as:
-> tkinter for the GUI
-> sqlite3 for the database
-> matplotlib or seaborn for visualizations.


Project Structure:
----------------------

Organize your project into modules for better readability and maintainability.
------------------------------------------------------------------
Example structure:

to_do_notes_app/
├── app.py
├── database.py
├── gui.py
├── notes.py
├── tasks.py
├── visualization.py
├── utils.py
└── requirements.txt
-----------------------------------------------------------------

Database Module (database.py):

Set up a SQLite database to store tasks and notes.

Example functions:
create_tables()
add_task()
delete_task()
add_note()
delete_note()
fetch_all_tasks()
fetch_all_notes().

-------------------------------------------------------------
GUI Module (gui.py):
--------------------
Create the main application window using tkinter.

Define different frames or windows for tasks and notes.

--------------------------------------------------------------
Tasks Module (tasks.py):
------------------------

Define functions and classes to manage tasks.

Example classes: Task, TaskManager.

--------------------------------------------------------------
Notes Module (notes.py):
------------------------
Define functions and classes to manage notes.
Example classes: Note, NoteManager.

--------------------------------------------------------------
Visualization Module (visualization.py):
----------------------------------------

Create functions to generate visual reports.

Example functions: plot_tasks_by_priority(), plot_tasks_over_time().

----------------------------------------------------------------
Utility Module (utils.py):
--------------------------

Define helper functions for common operations.

Example functions: get_current_time(), validate_input().

-----------------------------------------------------------------
Main Application (app.py):
--------------------------
Integrate all modules and run the application.